                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/25424: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General in Martinique (<persName type="from"
                            >Malige</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort-de-France</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-10T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 10, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>479. From Reber. My 473, November 8, and 478, November 10.<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d639fn10">Latter not printed.</note> Robert has just informed me
                    that Vichy has expressed its desire that he maintain relations with the United
                    States on the basis of the agreement reached November 7 and has entrusted him
                    with carrying on official relations of the French possessions in the Western
                    Hemisphere. [Reber.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Malige</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
